Traditional Harvesting Process
Manual labor is the norm â€“ people use khurpis (small hand hoes) or kodalos (pickaxes) to gently dig up the soil.

Families and neighbors often help each otherâ€”harvesting is a communal activity.

After digging, potatoes are gathered, sorted by size, and dried in the sun for a day or two before storage.

Potatoes are stored in cool, dark spacesâ€”sometimes in mud-plastered storage pits or barns to last through winter.

